snippet.title: Amber Ruffin Got Rejected by 'SNL' and Immediately Hired by Seth Meyers
snippet.description:
Comedian Amber Ruffin explained to Ellen how she auditioned for "Saturday Night Live," and didn't get cast. Fortunately, former "SNL” head writer Seth Meyers called her the next day to hire her on his own show, "Late Night with Seth Meyers." Amber also talked about hosting her late-night talk show, “The Amber Ruffin Show,” and how she's been into comedy since she was a kid.
